President Obama expresses his gratitude for Mike Leiter's service to the nation and acknowledges the difficulty of his decision to resign from the National Counterterrorism Center. Leiter has led the Center with dedication and determination during challenging times, and his contributions to the nation's safety and security are highly valued. Leiter has been a trusted advisor to the President and the national security team, providing valuable insights into terrorist activities. The President is confident that Leiter's departure will leave the Center and the nation better equipped to confront the terrorist threats they face.